<explanation interaction="true" hide="yes">
<para> (A) is correct because the function of the expression <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> so
again </emphasis>is to highlight the fact that the librarian is repeating
something he has already stated. The student is asked to select a subtopic,
not the title of an article (B). He does not ask the student to change her
topic (C). It is clear that the librarian understands what the student wants
(D), not that he is unsure.</para>
